# Top-level test / build dependencies for the EdgeFirst Client.
#
# Edit this file to add or pin packages, then regenerate the
# hash-locked ``requirements.txt`` (committed alongside) with:
#
#     pip install pip-tools
#     pip-compile --generate-hashes -o requirements.txt requirements.in
#
# Use *bounded ranges* here, not exact pins: the hash-locked
# ``requirements.txt`` already nails every artifact down by SHA-256
# so reproducible builds are guaranteed by the lock file (which is
# what ``pip install --require-hashes`` consumes in CI; satisfies
# SonarCloud githubactions:S8544). Allowing minor/patch ranges here
# lets ``pip-compile`` pick up upstream security fixes on the next
# refresh without anyone hand-editing each line.
#
# Upper bounds stop short of the next major release to avoid
# accidentally adopting breaking changes — refresh deliberately when
# the package's own changelog says it is safe.
